Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.07,0:00:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The experiments at Red Rose Mansion are still continuing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.01,0:00:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The devil now has\Nan apprentice.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.92,0:00:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The man with glasses...\NThe su{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.82,0:00:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Peter. .. Čapek...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.70,0:00:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He...is trying to\Ncontrol the devil.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.96,0:01:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.71,0:01:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He got away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.47,0:03:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.94,0:03:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:03:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.52,0:03:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.89,0:04:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.13,0:04:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky.\NYou just sprained your ankle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,From the looks of it,\Nyou didn't hit your head hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.33,0:04:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not an expert like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.17,0:04:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You know about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.64,0:04:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma,\Na brilliant neurosurgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.77,0:04:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.48,0:04:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.91,0:04:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a dentist here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.25,0:04:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan Kolas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.41,0:04:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I happened to see you get hit by a car.\NThe car took off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.52,0:04:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You should rest more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.36,0:04:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm troubling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wandering out on those legs and\Ngetting caught around here by the police
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.30,0:04:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,would trouble me even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.10,0:04:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"Around here?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.17,0:04:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Frankfurt's\NTurkish neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.71,0:04:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Turkish neighborhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.28,0:04:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I should say that it was\Nthe Turkish neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.81,0:05:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of this area has been\Ncleared for redevelopment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.12,0:05:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the Turks who lived here\Nhave moved away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.16,0:05:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A while back, when right-wing\Nextremists tried to burn it down,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.03,0:05:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we all joined together\Nto fight them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the Café Bahir gone too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.13,0:05:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.84,0:05:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know this area?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.47,0:05:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. A little.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.07,0:05:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, if you can get up, would\Nyou like to have dinner over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Meals taste better when\Neaten together, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.78,0:05:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we're having Vietnamese food.\NMinh made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.39,0:05:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pho ga and cha gio tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.23,0:05:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Minh's Vietnamese food is\Nexceptional. Don't be shy. Eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.33,0:05:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.34,0:05:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I love pork,\Nbut the Turks forbid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Czech food isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.81,0:06:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because Milan's\Nterrible at cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.82,0:06:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.22,0:06:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone takes turns to make\Nthe food from his or her homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.79,0:06:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty extravagant to be eating\Nfood from different countries every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.12,0:06:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.36,0:06:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, you're Japanese,\Naren't you? How's Japanese food?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.83,0:06:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese food, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.73,0:06:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NMake some next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.90,0:06:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...katsudon uses pork.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And sushi... There are some\Npeople who can't eat raw fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How about Oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Chicken covered\Nwith eggs and sauce on rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it called an "oyakodon"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.59,0:06:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The chicken is the parent\Nand the egg is the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why it's called\Na "parent-and-child bowl"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.39,0:06:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knew Japanese food\Nhad a sense of humor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:06:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How amusing to refer to chicken\Nand eggs as parent and child.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.94,0:07:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.64,0:07:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the food not to your liking?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.11,0:07:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.01,0:07:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Such delicious food...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a fun meal...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really been\Nsuch a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.67,0:07:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Tenma
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.34,0:07:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.48,0:07:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How long will it take\Nuntil I can walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have the time to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.53,0:08:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter. ..Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.60,0:08:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.24,0:08:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A report of Peter Čapek's\Nmovements?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.31,0:08:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew it was odd,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The police didn't gather here\Nso they could catch you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.42,0:08:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The police were on\Nthe look out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.06,0:08:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm...going to kill.. .\NPeter Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.17,0:08:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.67,0:08:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd. I used to be able to\Nmake ones that flew really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.98,0:08:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan is good at making\Npaper airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.71,0:08:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They fly smoothly over\Nto that roof there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.18,0:08:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.58,0:08:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan always says to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:08:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He always promises us...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.96,0:09:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Soon enough, we'll go much further\Nthan those rooftops.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.76,0:09:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll go to Turkey, Vietnam,\Neven to the Czech Republic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.50,0:09:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll all go and see each other's\Nhomelands together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.80,0:09:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.97,0:09:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.18,0:09:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't it fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.51,0:09:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm...going to kill Peter Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Mr. Milan,\Nwhy would you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.66,0:09:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That man...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That man Peter Čapek\Nis a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.97,0:09:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1989, the night before the collapse\Nof communism in Czechoslovakia,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.97,0:09:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he escaped into this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.31,0:09:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Čapek settled here\Nin Frankfurt
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and began giving lessons\Nas a German language teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.01,0:10:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a quiet man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.08,0:10:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But after a while, there was a change\Nin the children who attended his classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.76,0:10:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One by one, the children who took\Nhis classes began to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.63,0:10:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they began to display\Nextremely violent behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.23,0:10:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, one day,\Nthere was a massive violent eruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.84,0:10:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked like the children\Nwere trying to kill each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I talked to the boy who was\Nthe ringleader of the incident
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.51,0:10:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,at the place where\Nhe was being detained.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.41,0:10:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He mumbled, "I want to go back\Nto the recitals immediately."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.49,0:10:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Recitals?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That night,\Nthe boy killed himself inside his cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.99,0:10:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He was my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.36,0:10:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Čapek disappeared from\Nthe town during the riot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.90,0:10:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The next time he appeared in town,\Nhe was like a different man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He was leading an underground\Norganization in Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He had allied himself\Nwith right-wing extremists
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.65,0:11:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and he began to eject the Turks\Nand other foreigners from this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.39,0:11:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what\Nhe's trying to do here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.26,0:11:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But the pinnacle of\Nhis violence was in 1996,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.93,0:11:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when he tried to burn down\Nthe Turkish neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.10,0:11:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You know about this incident,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.00,0:11:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. From the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.67,0:11:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in this town formed\Na neighborhood watch group
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.28,0:11:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and tried to fight them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But in just three months,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.98,0:11:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the five leaders of the neighborhood\Nwatch died in strange ways one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are the five who died?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.86,0:11:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Suleiman's son, Tung's father,\NMinh's husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.93,0:11:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mustafa's son,\Nand Shemel's father...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.20,0:12:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.87,0:12:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They were murdered\Nby Peter Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.34,0:12:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why\Nyou're watching Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who's going\Nto kill Čapek...is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.03,0:12:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hold on, I think this one is\Ngoing to work much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.33,0:12:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.40,0:12:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No. If we try...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.53,0:12:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you try hard,\Nimpossible is still impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.57,0:12:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. There's no way that we can\Ngo on a trip to Turkey and Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.34,0:12:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to go on a trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.21,0:12:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We can continue to live\Nwith Milan and Tung.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.72,0:12:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.36,0:12:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll fly this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:12:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.43,0:12:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.03,0:13:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! It's flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.73,0:13:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's impossible\Nto make one
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.37,0:13:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes beyond that rooftop\Nlike Mr. Milan can.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.57,0:13:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's flying, somewhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.84,0:13:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you glad\Nyou didn't give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.68,0:13:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,– Yeah !\N– Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.81,0:13:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.91,0:13:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.64,0:13:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you put the gun\Nthat was in my drawer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.81,0:13:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a chance\Nto shoot Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.32,0:13:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.88,0:13:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me back my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.39,0:14:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.39,0:14:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't give you back your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.26,0:14:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the gun that\Nwas in your coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.47,0:14:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do the job with a gun that\NI've trained with and that I'm used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.54,0:14:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.14,0:14:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a family now.\NYou shouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.45,0:14:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been following Čapek's\Nmovements for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no better chance\Nto go after him than now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.35,0:14:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop, Mr. Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.52,0:14:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you not to interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.09,0:14:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you take your revenge now,\Nthe dead won't return.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.10,0:14:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore...\NYou have to think about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.77,0:14:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no right\Nto tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.27,0:14:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Milan...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.04,0:14:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the same, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.01,0:14:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.82,0:15:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If what you claim is true,\Nwe're doing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.19,0:15:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't always like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.03,0:15:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The man I knew...\Nwasn't a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.63,0:15:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter Čapek and I are childhood\Nfriends from the same county.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.84,0:15:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I invited him to this country!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.94,0:15:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think\Nis across the border?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.28,0:15:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.01,0:15:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I shouldn't,\Nbut do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.19,0:15:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard it's a wonderful place\Nbeyond the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.36,0:15:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a town where\Nit's bright all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true, Peter?\NWho did you hear that from?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.46,0:15:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gregor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.06,0:15:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.93,0:15:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They say that\Nacross the border,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.87,0:15:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,there are things that can ruin a man\Njust like what happened to Mr. Gregor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.24,0:15:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that\Nruins people, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.94,0:16:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.01,0:16:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to see\Nsomething like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.65,0:16:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.18,0:16:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It caught the wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really good, Milan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.48,0:16:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's flying! It's flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.09,0:16:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing ! That could really\Ncross the border!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.42,0:16:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at what's on\Nthe other side for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We were raised in a town on the\NCzechoslovakian and Austrian border.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.57,0:16:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the son of a laborer.\NHe was the son of a bureaucrat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.77,0:16:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But, oddly, we got along.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.01,0:16:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1989, when the Czechoslovakian\NCommunist regime collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the one who helped him defect. ..\Nwas me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.48,0:16:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The one that brought that devil\Nto this land was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.10,0:17:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was worried about you during\Nthe Soviet invasion last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.94,0:17:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people I knew were\Ndragged off, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.37,0:17:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm here safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.01,0:17:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.31,0:17:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Me? I'm scraping by here and\Nthere as a rookie dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.28,0:17:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan's a dentist, huh? You were always\Nskillful with your hands, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.49,0:17:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the kind of skills that get you\Nahead in the world, like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.43,0:17:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, the reason I kept my position\Neven after the Soviets came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.66,0:17:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was probably because\NI'm good at getting ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.27,0:17:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I even had a lot of fun\Nduring the "Prague Spring."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.84,0:17:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I even got to go to the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.04,0:17:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked about that when\Nwe were young, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.91,0:17:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We wondered what it was like\Non the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.55,0:17:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get your answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.41,0:17:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.62,0:17:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.28,0:17:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing.\NOn this side or that side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.99,0:17:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This country is wrong. But that doesn't\Nmean that the other side is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.83,0:17:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.09,0:18:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that I'm good at\Ngetting ahead in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.00,0:18:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But actually, there's someone\Nwho saw something in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.33,0:18:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.50,0:18:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When you meet him,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.47,0:18:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he's so wonderful that you stop\Ncaring about your present situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.14,0:18:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when I had concluded that\Nthere was nothing in either country.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.31,0:18:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He showed me a light\NI never knew existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.28,0:18:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He will bring forth\Nsomething entirely new.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.15,0:18:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And? What's he\Ngoing to bring forth?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.09,0:18:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll bring forth? Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.00,0:18:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be something frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.34,0:18:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking back on it, something inside\Nof him might have started coming apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.18,0:18:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me back my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.79,0:18:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. I'll give you\Nback your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.56,0:19:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Mr. Milan...\Nyou can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.13,0:19:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't stop me.\NI'm going to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.46,0:19:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a family you're with,\Nright now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.03,0:19:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's killed several members\Nfrom this family.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.80,0:19:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They were killed because\NI brought him to this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.28,0:19:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Even my son...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.92,0:19:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,After that attempt\Nto burn down this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.69,0:19:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there was one person the Turks\Nspeak highly of, even to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.32,0:19:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a Japanese man who\Ndesperately tended to the wounded...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.63,0:19:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and tried his best\Nto put out the fires.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you isn't it, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.70,0:19:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.00,0:19:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you're trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.07,0:19:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the same as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.81,0:19:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going. It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.98,0:20:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If I let this opportunity go,\NI might never get another chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.39,0:20:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Milan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.66,0:20:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for trying to stop me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.46,0:20:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was in your shoes...\NI doubt I could stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.83,0:20:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.37,0:20:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.87,0:20:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. This is really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.84,0:21:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese Oyakodon\Nis really delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.58,0:21:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your leg all right?\NShall I help you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.79,0:21:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'll be finished with\Nyour portion soon, Mrs. Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.26,0:21:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan sure is late.\NI think he should be home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.76,0:21:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. It's best to eat it\Nas soon as it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.46,0:21:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,– I'll make Mr. Milan's portion later.\N{\i1}– Next in the news...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.10,0:21:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,– Really? Then I'll leave you to it.\N{\i1}– At about 11 A.M.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.40,0:21:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}at the Roedelheim Convention Center\Nin Frankfurt,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.40,0:21:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there was an incident where a man\Nwith a handgun, opened fire.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.51,0:21:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Police who were providing security for\Nthe convention shot and killed the gunman.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.98,0:21:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There were\Nno other casualties.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.08,0:21:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But due to the large number of important\Nfigures present at the convention center,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.92,0:21:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there was significant cause for\Nconcern among the attendees.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.02,0:21:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The gunman's identity and\Nmotives are still unknown.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.06,0:21:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We now turn to a clip of the incident\Nthat happened to be caught on tape.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.20,0:21:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone says it's delicious.\NIt's a hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.37,0:22:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish Milan would\Ncome home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.78,0:22:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And now the footage\Nof the incident.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.32,0:22:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That man...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.49,0:22:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's Red Rose Mansion's...\NThat's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.76,0:22:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't keep secrets from him.{\i0}
